## GAP 2 — MAVEN BUILD PASSES IN TOOL BUT FAILS IN TEKTON (compilation errors)

### What is wrong
The shell script checks Maven exit code only (`$? -eq 0`).
Maven can exit 0 with compilation errors in certain multi-module setups
where one module fails but the build is not set to fail-fast.
Tekton runs the full build with stricter settings and catches what the tool misses.

### Fix in nexusiq_auto_vuln_fix.sh

Replace the simple exit code check with a full output scan:

```bash
# Find the Maven build invocation. It will look like:
mvn package -f "$REPO_DIR/pom.xml" ... > "$BUILD_LOG" 2>&1
BUILD_EXIT=$?

# REPLACE the success check with:
build_truly_passed() {
    local log="$1"
    local exit_code="$2"

    # Exit code must be 0
    if [ "$exit_code" -ne 0 ]; then
        return 1
    fi

    # Even if exit 0, scan log for compilation failures
    if grep -qiE \
        "BUILD FAILURE|COMPILATION ERROR|cannot find symbol|\
        error: package .* does not exist|error: cannot access|\
        ClassNotFoundException|NoClassDefFoundError|\
        symbol not found|incompatible types" \
        "$log" 2>/dev/null; then
        log "[BUILD] Exit code 0 but compilation errors detected in log."
        log "[BUILD] This fix would fail in Tekton. Treating as build failure."
        return 1
    fi

    # Must contain explicit BUILD SUCCESS
    if ! grep -q "BUILD SUCCESS" "$log" 2>/dev/null; then
        log "[BUILD] Exit code 0 but BUILD SUCCESS not found. Treating as failure."
        return 1
    fi

    return 0
}

if build_truly_passed "$BUILD_LOG" "$BUILD_EXIT"; then
    log "[BUILD] Verified: BUILD SUCCESS with no compilation errors."
    # proceed to push
else
    log "[BUILD] Build failed or has compilation errors. Rolling back POM."
    cp "$REPO_DIR/pom.xml.bak" "$REPO_DIR/pom.xml"
    # record rollback
    echo "$ga:$safe_version" >> "$ROLLBACK_FILE"
fi
```

